<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-6DCC5972-289B-417E-8F90-C60081E01EA0" version="4" lang="en-US"?><tsTroubleshooting xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-6DCC5972-289B-417E-8F90-C60081E01EA0" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" domains="(topic tsTroubleshooting)                            (topic hi-d)    (topic sdlVariables-c)                             (topic ut-d)                             (topic indexing-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c tsTroubleshooting oceTroubleshooting-c)   " class="- topic/topic tsTroubleshooting/tsTroubleshooting "><title translate="no" class="- topic/title ">250001 Ink delivery to printhead failed</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-B87BF88B-91B2-4C27-A55C-91B9B6986C8A"><p class="- topic/p "> Ink delivery to printhead failed (PH1, PH3, PH4, PH5, PH6). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After starting the ink supply, it is expected to be stopped within a given time. When this doesn't occur this error is reported. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This error can have to 2 different root causes. 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The ink was not transported to the printhead in time 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The level sensor in the printhead didn’t detect the received ink. 
</p></li></ol><p class="- topic/p "> The flowchart below can be used to minimize the MTTR and reduce the change of a second visit. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-E6ACBFE2-B06A-42E1-9F98-D004BC924E73"><title class="- topic/title "/><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-CE33D010-398B-40C7-AB2B-8E98AA53FC96-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-CE33D010-398B-40C7-AB2B-8E98AA53FC96-svg.svg"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Decision 1) : New installation</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Did the error occur during the installation of a new printhead ( Z-0402 ) or new ink tube ( Z-0502 )? 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-0C486A15-46FC-4085-9D5A-6858298BA622"><p class="- topic/p ">In some rare cases it's known the ink valve of a printhead might be blocked (even if the valve is opened). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In those cases please replace the valve by a new one (1070078229) or by removing the blockade by pushing a Torx-screwdriver through the valve. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Don't replace the printhead. 
</p></note><p class="- topic/p "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Action 1) : Mark as empty</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Mark printheads as empty and restart filling. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> See 
<xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="SDS04-6-020" href="GUID-76FA0F98-276D-43D0-B9BF-6ABC38D906A7.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 04-6-020 Mark printhead(s) as empty [Special Tests]?>04-6-020 Mark printhead(s) as empty [Special Tests]</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Decision 2) : Closed valves</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Check if the ink valves or air clamps on the printheads are closed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Action 2) : Open valves</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Open valves on carriage. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Open clamps on air hose, rub the air hose to make sure the hose is open. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Decision 3) : Warning 290020</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Has warning 290020 appeared sometime before error 250001? 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Filter polluted with ink: mark the head as empty, replace the ink tube. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Action 3): Clean ink system</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The ink in the printer is expired, this might result is clogged or viscous ink. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Clean ink system 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Decision 4) : Warning 290005</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Has warning 290005 appeared sometime before error 250001? 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Action 4): Replace pump tubes</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Check replace pump tubes 
