</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Decision 8) : Leakage</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Are there any traces of leaked ink inside the machine? (example: Valves, not connected tubes, ruptured tubes) 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Action 8): Repair leakage</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Replace leaking valves 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Reconnect tube 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Replace ruptured tubes 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Decision 9) : Clogged ink tube</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Disconnect the ink tube from printheads 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> (See<xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="02ADJU004" href="GUID-0A9015C3-DC1C-417D-8B80-D6AE9F8C4B83.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 The (expired) ink replacement procedure including flushing tubes?>02 The ink replacement procedure</xref> , Chapter 3. Refill the system with new ink : Step 7 - 14) 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Disconnect the pump tube from the ink tube. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Use a syringe to pull ink through the ink tubes. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> If ink is flowing freely through the ink tube, reconnect tubes and fill ink tubes 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> (See<xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="02ADJU004" href="GUID-0A9015C3-DC1C-417D-8B80-D6AE9F8C4B83.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 The (expired) ink replacement procedure including flushing tubes?>02 The ink replacement procedure</xref> , Chapter 3. Refill the system with new ink : Step 15 - 27) 
