</p><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="04DISA002" href="GUID-75F1003D-F727-49BD-88A7-1CEF7223F097.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>04 How to replace a (failing) printhead: Overview document</xref> 
</p></entry><entry align="left" class="- topic/entry " colname="col5" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "> 
<xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="04COMP01" href="GUID-DF50154C-9672-4767-A789-CF04D38BD803.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>04 The components of the printhead</xref> 
</p></entry><entry align="left" class="- topic/entry " colname="col6" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "> 
<xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="04ELEC01" href="GUID-A78436AA-F839-4445-B996-2874CF9AAD16.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>04 Electrical diagram printheads</xref> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Decision 11) : Air filter clogged</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Check if air filter of printhead contains ink. If the tube is completely filled with ink the air filter will be colored (see example below) 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-38B34359-7DF9-47AD-B198-B99ED43AAC77"><title class="- topic/title "/><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-A4F46D0B-DB2D-4205-91EE-728E9F927DD1-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-A4F46D0B-DB2D-4205-91EE-728E9F927DD1-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">In some cases the tube is not completely filled with ink and the air tube needs to be inspected at the bottom of the printhead (near the ink reservoir). This can be done by gently sliding the sleeve a few centimeters upward (see below). This way the transparent air tube will be visible. If this is colored there is ink inside the air tube. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Check the condition of the tubes at the backside of the polluted airfilter 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-251770FC-87D9-413C-A281-9F28CDEC5329"><p class="- topic/p ">If Ink passed the inkfilter into the manifold, no pressure can be given because the manifolds are blocked with ink. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">There will be no air leakage. also the observation is that the closed ink just flows through the printheads instead of being kept into the heads. 
</p></note><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-0DECD449-647C-4FA2-A985-B8DEF9AF98E1"><title class="- topic/title "/><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-94613DEE-6C6F-4645-9E36-E76D2A0250B5-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-94613DEE-6C6F-4645-9E36-E76D2A0250B5-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Action 11A) : Replace air hose</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> See 
<xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="04DISAAIRHOSE001" href="GUID-5A857576-AEE8-4F06-9521-73897D6BB258.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 04 How to remove the air hose?>04 How to remove the air hose</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Action 11B) : Replace Boiler unit</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> See 
<xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="04DISA001" href="GUID-A0CE2B4B-139D-421F-9933-A4955E7DD62B.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 04 How to remove the boiler unit?>04 How to remove the boiler unit</xref>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Decision 12) : Out of other options</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Check if ink is coming out of recirculation circuit, if yes replace VALVE-TUBE-ASSY 
<xref class="- topic/xref " format="dita" href="GUID-C7CD297B-5F83-4EE0-85D2-E388D7CF879B.xml" scope="local" type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>02 How to remove the white ink 3-way valve</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If all previous actions did not solve the error and the error occurs on the white printhead, please check the 02Y5 (YMS_CAR_RECIRC_VA). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">You can do this by performing SDS 02-6-010 White Ink Recirculation (Special Test). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If this did not solve the error, replace printhead.
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Action 12): Remove printhead</b> 
